@page "/about-us"
<PageTitle>SOAR - About us</PageTitle>
<h1 class="text-center page-header">About us</h1>

<div class="d-flex flex-column gap-5 m-4">
    <BoxShadowContainer>
        <h2 class="text-center">Mission</h2>
        <p class="indent">
            Our mission at SOAR is to incorporate collaborative approaches to achieve our overarching goal
            of conserving and restoring coral reefs and ultimately our oceans.
        </p>
        <p>
            We accomplish this by embracing sustainability, holistic perspectives, and partnerships with diverse stakeholders
            to drive positive change and ensure the long-term health, resilience, and well-being of these vital ecosystems.
        </p>
    </BoxShadowContainer>
</div>

<div class="d-flex flex-column gap-5 m-4">
    <BoxShadowContainer>
        <h2 class="text-center">Who we are</h2>
        <p class="indent">
            We are a pioneering organization dedicated to advancing marine conservation through innovative approaches.
        </p>
        <p>
            Focused on the development of in situ rearing mariculture systems, SOAR aims to harness the potential of sea
            urchins for restorative purposes.
        </p>
        <p>
            By carefully cultivating urchins in their natural habitats, SOAR seeks to contribute to the enhancement of
            marine ecosystems, particularly coral reefs, through the ecologically sound deployment of these sea creatures
        </p>
    </BoxShadowContainer>
</div>

